This paper deals with the design of relay assisted ad hoc networks, which is a topic related to network infrastructure and communication protocols. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also considers power allocation and relaying strategies, which are topics related to information theory and signal processing, making cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.SY (Systems and Control) likely categories as well. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of compress-and-forward, which is a technique related to multimedia communication, making cs.MM (Multimedia) a possible category. Finally, the paper discusses the optimization of relay nodes, which is a topic related to computer engineering, making cs.CE (Computer Engineering) a possible category as well.
